# Documentation boundaries (three tiers)

**Critical rule.** When editing related files, if you notice existing code or docs that violate this rule — even outside your current task — **flag it to the user as a high concern** before or alongside your main work. Do not silently ignore, copy the pattern, or defer without mention.

Assume **thousands of third-party CPS formats**. No generic doc can host wire-mapping tables for even one format, however well labelled. Wire detail lives **only** under `docs/reference/<format>/`. Generic docs **link out**; they never embed format tables.

Pairs with [vendor-boundaries.mdc](vendor-boundaries.mdc) (code/model) and [format-agnostic-docs.mdc](format-agnostic-docs.mdc) (wording). Read [AGENTS.md — Vendor boundaries](../../AGENTS.md#vendor-boundaries) for the code side.

## Three tiers

| Tier | Location | Allowed | Forbidden |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **1 — Internal model** | [`docs/features/data-model/`](../../docs/features/data-model/), other feature docs describing *our* entities | Field types, null semantics, mode applicability, UUID FK rules | CSV column names, format wire values (`P2`, `Master`, `75%`), import/export rule tables |
| **2 — Domain-neutral reference** | [`docs/reference/bands.md`](../../docs/reference/bands.md), [`channel-modes.md`](../../docs/reference/channel-modes.md), [`display-conventions.md`](../../docs/reference/display-conventions.md), other `docs/reference/*.md` at the **root** (not in a format subfolder) | RF/amateur domain facts; UI mode taxonomy; **one-line cross-links** to the import/export hub or `docs/reference/<format>/` | Wire-mapping tables — including a section titled “OpenGD77 mapping”; enumerating format-specific column headers |
| **3 — Format wire reference** | [`docs/reference/opengd77/`](../../docs/reference/opengd77/) today; siblings when shipped (e.g. `docs/reference/dm32/`) | Full column ↔ internal type tables, power ladders, squelch strings, MHz formatting, TOT step, tone wire forms | Claiming these rules apply to other formats |

Adapter code mirrors tier 3: wire strings and ladders stay in `src/lib/import/<format>/` and `src/lib/export/<format>/` only — not in `src/models/`, generic `src/lib/`, or tier 1/2 docs.

## Hard rules

- **Do not** create new wire-mapping files at `docs/reference/` root (e.g. `power-levels.md`, `squelch-levels.md`, `tones.md`) — not even with an “OpenGD77” subsection inside.
- **Do not** add wire tables to tier 1 or tier 2 files. If a table maps a CPS column to an internal field, it belongs in tier 3 under the correct format directory.
- **New format wire docs** go under `docs/reference/<format>/`, indexed from that format’s `README.md`.

## Cross-reference pattern (tier 1 and 2)

One sentence + URL — no table in the generic file:

> Format-specific wire mapping lives in the [import/export hub](../../docs/features/import-export/README.md) and per-format references under `docs/reference/<format>/` (OpenGD77: [channels.md](../../docs/reference/opengd77/channels.md)).

When the sentence is about **all** external formats, link the hub and the `<format>/` pattern — not OpenGD77 alone as the definition of the internal model.

## Quick check

Before saving a doc change, ask:

1. **Which tier?** Internal type → tier 1; RF/UI domain with no CPS → tier 2; CSV column or wire string → tier 3 under `docs/reference/<format>/` only.
2. **10,000-format test:** would this file still make sense if we supported thousands of CPS formats? If it lists one format’s wire values, it belongs in that format’s directory.
3. **Tables:** any import/export/wire column table outside `docs/reference/<format>/` → move it; generic files get a link only.

## Examples

**Unacceptable (tier 2 file with embedded wire table):**

```markdown
## Power mapping
| OpenGD77 wire | Internal |
| Master | null |
| P2 | 25 |
```

**Acceptable (tier 2 — link only):**

```markdown
OpenGD77 power column mapping: [opengd77/channels.md](../reference/opengd77/channels.md).
```

**Acceptable (tier 1 — internal semantics only):**

```markdown
`power`: percentage 0–100, or `null` for radio default (no fixed level selected).
```

**Acceptable (tier 3 — OpenGD77 wire table):**

In `docs/reference/opengd77/channels.md` or a sibling file under that directory only.
